trespass
Interface Trespasser<T>

public interface Trespasser<T>

This marker interface must be extended by any interface used to define a dynamic proxy that can be created using the Factory.

Interfaces extending InternalProxy will declare method signatures that should map existing methods and/or fields that are declared in a target class. Each InternalProxy interface must specify one single target class by annotating the interface declaration with ProxyClass.

To map a method in the interface with the actual method in the target class, just make sure to declare a signature that is identical to the target. For example:

@ProxyClass(System.class) interface SystemProxy extends InternalProxy {
long nanoTime(); // will be implicitly mapped to target System.nanoTime()
}
